<title>FRANCE: Films in competition at 1997 Cannes festival.</title>
<headline>Films in competition at 1997 Cannes festival.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-04-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following list of films competing for the Golden Palm award at the May 7-18 Cannes festival was announced on Tuesday:</p>
<p>- &quot;The Ice Storm&quot; - Ang Lee (Taiwan)</p>
<p>- &quot;Il principe di Hombourg di Einrich Von Kleist&quot; (The Prince of Hamburg by Heinrich Von Kleist) - Marco Bellocchio (Italy)</p>
<p>- &quot;Call it love&quot; - Nick Kassavetes (USA)</p>
<p>- &quot;The Brave&quot; - Johnny Depp (USA)</p>
<p>- &quot;The Sweet Hereafter&quot; - Atom Egoyan (Canada)</p>
<p>- &quot;Funny games&quot; - Michael Haneke (Austria)</p>
<p>- &quot;L.A. confidential&quot; - Curtis Hanson (USA)</p>
<p>- &quot;La femme defendue&quot; (The Banned Woman) - Philippe Harel (France)</p>
<p>- &quot;Unagi&quot; (The Eel) - Shohei Imamura (Japan)</p>
<p>- &quot;Assassins&quot; - Matthieu Kassovitz (France)</p>
<p>- &quot;The Well&quot; - Samantha Lang (Australia)</p>
<p>- &quot;Nil By Mouth&quot; - Gary Oldman (Britain)</p>
<p>- &quot;Kiny et Adams&quot; (Kiny and Adams) - Idrissa Ouedraogo (Burkina Faso)</p>
<p>- &quot;Western&quot; - Manuel Poirier (France)</p>
<p>- &quot;La Tregua&quot; (The Truce) - Francesco Rosi (Italy)</p>
<p>- &quot;Happy Together&quot; - Wong Kar-Wai (Hong Kong)</p>
<p>- &quot;The End Of Violence&quot; - Wim Wenders (Germany)</p>
<p>- &quot;Welcome To Sarajevo&quot; Michael Winterbottom (Britain)</p>
<p>- &quot;Keep Cool&quot; - Zhang Yimou (China).</p>
<p>Opening film: &quot;Le Cinquieme Element&quot; (The Fifth Element) - Luc Besson (France)</p>
<p>Closing film: (outside competition) - &quot; Absolute Power&quot; - Clint Eastwood (USA).</p>
